result.name: Dor Lee Man

reviews.text: Good Chinese vergi restaurant for daily meal.

Great affordable local family style Chinese vegetarian food. Tasty and fast service. Love the set meals served all day from 11am til late, only from hk$42 for a main dish including rice and soup, with option to change rice to congee or rice noodles in soup. 

They have a la carte menu as well, but expect good standard down to earth family style dishes and NOT 5 star hotel excellent presentation.

Photo is Singapore noodles hk$50 and mains combo from food of the day board hk$33 (usually hk$42 If a set with rice & soup)

This is like my 2nd home, I come here 2-5 times a week when I can.

Booking only available for large groups.
Very popular, especially on new moon and full moon or Buddhist dates.

You know this vegetarian restaurant goes beyond the usual tofu and broccoli when you witness firsthand the extensive lines of people queuing down the street waiting to get a seat and, the wait won't disappoint, as this eatery serves some of the most delicious, if not the best vegetarian dishes (employing ingredients sourced locally) that I've ever tasted. Dishes are presented fast and hot in an eclectic mix of stainless steel and china bowls, cooked to perfection and served with attitude, you need to remind yourself that you came for the food not the service, and the people hovering over your table are not being rude, they just want to eat too, and they're standing over you because they want your seat. All of that said, the food served here will please even the most dedicated of carnivores, just remember, it's the food you came for which on it's own would be a solid five/5!

Great vegetarian food served piping hot!! It's a small place which seats around 40 people, menu is mostly in Chinese with some dishes in English and it gets busy so you may have to share a table. On to the food! To save you some time, the dishes that were absolute winners in my opinion were the fried lotus cakes. Not greasy and the firm, chewy texture was really satisfying. Order the Tung Choi (water spinach) which is served in a rich, spicy, umami laden fermented bean curd sauce. The aroma of the chili kicks in without being overpowering on the heat. The salt and pepper king oyster mushrooms were firm, and perfectly cooked. The delicately flavoured veg only soup served at the beginning of the meal compliments the heavy flavors and is a good palate cleanser. Portions are BIG so order carefully! Big plates, big flavors all packed in a small shop. Can't go wrong!

I am a fan of Dor Lee Man Veggie Restaurant.  Often, I come here after a hard hike that ends in Tai Po.  For one person, they conveniently offer sets that include soup, rice and choice of 2 dishes combined.  Even though there are quite a bit of reconstituted veggie ingredients, it is still possible to avoid them as the restaurant does offer actual vegetable dishes.  I ordered yam and lotus root pancake with peanut, lotus root (again) and tofu sheets.  
A bit of disappointment is the dish was room temperature, but for HK$44 a set, I can't really complain.

result.adr_address: 香港大埔寶鄉街43號
result.name: 多利民素食

reviews.text: 全大埔最好食的素食店，不過大埔都好似無乜素食地方了，價錢公道，真的好味
客似雲来、經常冇位、味美家常、套飯抵食快靚正、價錢實惠、小菜巧手、員工勤快服務有效率，惟只供美吃不供閒談！

真不明白 呢個老闆是否修道之人 還是只是一個奸商 首先老闆超串超惡劣 大哥我們是要錢用餐而不是入來乞食 款式選擇不多 試過他們為了趕收工 其實都只不過是下午五點半 他們已經說什麼都沒有就 只有餐叫 我帶着老人家 勉為其難只好叫他們說的兩個餐。。。奉勸大家 如想吃素有所期望 請勿進入。。

不是有驚喜
而是有驚嚇
一言難盡。。。。
位於大埔宝鄉街多利民素食店，有曼魚素食，黃花鱼素食，雜扒素食等，當然羅漢齊素食不能決少，價錢算是便宜，午膳及晚餐時候，要排隊等候。
大眾化的素菜食館，價宜美味，斤兩十足。
